int lowerBound(int arr[], int n, int x) {
        int low=0;
        int high=n-1;
        int ans=n;
        while(low<=high){
            long long mid=(low+high)/2;
            if(arr[mid]>=x){
                ans=mid;
                high=mid-1;
            }
            else low=mid+1;
        }
        return ans;
}


Using Built-in Functions in C++
Given an array a of size n, find the lower bound of x using the built-in function
-> Arrays    lower_bound(a, a+n, x) - a
-> Vectors   lower_bound(a.begin(), a.end(), x) - a.begin();
